<a name="Creating a Test With New Questions">
<h4>
2.2.2.  Creating a Test With New Questions
</h4>
</a>
<p>
To create a test with new questions, the user selects <tt>Click to Add New Question</tt> as shown in Figure 2-4. Figure 2-4 also shows options available for the user to enter:
<ul>
<li>Test Name
<li>Class Name
<li>Time Limit
<li>Difficulty
<li>Grade Cutoffs
</ul>
The user can also select <tt>Save</tt> to save the test, or <tt>Back</tt> to return to the home screen.
<hr>
<a name="Edit Test Prompt">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/gen-test-empty-edit.png" style="height:50%">
</p>
<p align=center> Figure 2-4: Edit Test Prompt </p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>
<p>
To specify creation of a new question (rather than choosing from the question bank), the user selects <tt>New Question</tt> as shown in Figure 2-5. To save the test, the user selects <tt>Save</tt> as shown in Figure 2-4.
